The paper focuses on studying the success of online communities, which involves analyzing community properties and behaviors. This falls under the scope of social networks and social media (cs.SI), as well as computational social science (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SD). The paper also uses statistical analysis and machine learning to predict success, which could fall under computer science and game theory (cs.CC). Finally, the paper discusses the practical implications of their findings for the design of online platforms, which could fall under social and economic systems (cs.SOC).
